    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.9602/138c</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Archangel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-24T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>This is our cable No. 1. Subsequent cables will be numbered serially and in
                    cabling us you should similarly number your cables serially. Your official
                    cables to us should all be transmitted through the Department of State.</p>
                <p>1. The War Trade Board has appointed <persName corresp="#p_HA1">August
                        Heid</persName> its representative in Vladivostok and has sent him a cable
                    as quoted below, most of which will be applicable to Archangel region where you
                    have already been appointed to act as War Trade Board representative. The
                    $5,000,000 fund mentioned therein has no connection with the $6,000,000 fund
                    established some months ago for purchase of supplies <pb facs="0209" n="159"
                        xml:id="pg_159"/> in Russia. For your information our cable to <persName
                        corresp="#p_HA1">Heid</persName>, No. 1, reads substantially as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follow paragraphs 2 to 14 of telegram sent to <persName corresp="#p_HA1"
                        >Heid</persName> through the Ambassador in Japan, temporarily at
                    Vladivostok, October 10, 4 p.m., <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                        target="#pg_150">page 150</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
